Belgium: Edict in the name of Charles VI, Holy Roman Emperor, reorganises office of notary in the Habsburg Netherlands.
England: Gibraltar was captured by a combined Dutch and English fleet under the command of Admiral of the Fleet George Rooke. Battle of Blenheim: A combined English and Dutch army under the command of John Churchill, 1st Duke of Marlborough defeated the French army in Bavaria.
Estonia: Russian troops under czar Peter the Great captured Dorpat (Tartu) in the Great Northern War.
Philippine: North Borneo is ceded by the sultan of Brunei to the sultan of Sulu.
Poland:
Warsaw Confederation formed
Sandomierz Confederation formed
Election of Stanisław Leszczyński
